<TITLE> Nazmul Huda demands election schedule </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, May 4 (bdnews24.com)Former communications minister Nazmul Huda, now in jail, has demanded an announcement of a specific election schedule without delay. In a written statement made public by his lawyer Wednesday, barrister Huda said: The constitution did not give the caretaker government the authority of a guardian to shape the future of people." Huda appeared in court in an extortion case Wednesday. Huda sentenced to 19 years in jail in two cases said: "The responsibility of the caretaker government is to assist the Election Commission in holding an election within 90 days from the dissolution of parliament." In the statement, the BNP leader said: "The people will be benefit if the caretaker government understands its limitation and announces an election date soon." bdnew
